    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "65cc195c_d44b7858",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/autoscaler/autoscaler.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 94,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T19:07:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I\u0027m struggling with how to do this correctly without hard-coding dimensions for each scaler, but I really want to remove the requirement that at least one bot is online in order to know the scaler\u0027s dimensions.  One thing that is not included in this autoscaler is to always keep a minimum number of bots online, which we may want.  That would work around this issue, and also ensure that we go from completely idle/offline to running tasks a little quicker.  Thoughts?",
      "parentUuid": "5b185e04_413a75b0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 94,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 94,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "c44c54079486ea80ddd1c0fa36f0f4895754bd0e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "89d25578_c0896135",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/autoscaler/autoscaler.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 105,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-30T20:10:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This almost certainly doesn\u0027t matter, but...\n\nIf a candidate could be run by the bots of two different scalers, we will be double-counting that candidate. I believe this can happen with our current skcms tasks, which do not specify a machine_type. https://skia.googlesource.com/skcms/+/4642d9fe69e1ace1bb565a39f38fea9f776d8adb/infra/bots/tasks.json#52",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 105,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 105,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "c44c54079486ea80ddd1c0fa36f0f4895754bd0e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "47c52327_c23ca15a",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/autoscaler/autoscaler.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 105,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T19:07:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We have problems related to this in a couple of places, eg. triggering tasks, where we should really pair less-picky tasks with bots which are in lower demand.  I guess the current workaround is to use very specific dimensions in our task requests so that we don\u0027t usually overlap.  In this case, double-counting will result in our being more conservative with autoscaling, so I think it\u0027s okay (maybe a good thing initially).",
      "parentUuid": "89d25578_c0896135",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 105,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 105,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "c44c54079486ea80ddd1c0fa36f0f4895754bd0e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
